how do i get my dog toilet trained hi there i'm the proud owner of a ten weeks old puupy half german shephard half border collie however sometimes he still goes inside the house almost every time in the same spot i'm taking him out after every meal after every time we play and every time he wakes up when he does go outside i praise him straigth into heaven yet the creature doesn't seem to understand that going inside is not allowed or at least not so nice do i have to do something with that particular spot where he goes inside how do i teach him to signal me when he has to go right now he doesn't so and also how do you train him to keep it up so you don't have to get up every two and a half hours during the night thanks a lot gibrril hi gibrril weeks is still quite young to expect him to be fully housebroken for the place where he likes to go in the house get yourself a pet enzyme odor remover sold at petco and petsmart and follow the directions he is smelling his odor there and will continue to go there unless the odor is completely removed his bladder is still developing and he is not able to hold it for as long as an adult dog you'll notice as time goes on the longer he will be able to hold it you're doing great keep it up and before long he will be fully housebroken and you will be able to sleep through the night i tried the bell at the door thing too i had no luck again weeks is young and you just need to give him time to learn my dogs have learned to bark in a certain tone when they have to go out Housebreaking Obedience training Urinary incontinence Episodes of Lost (Season 1) G-Man (Half-Life) Fancy rat Sin City Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Cat Ocean's Twelve The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Skunk The Life and Times of Juniper Lee Guinea pig Keeshond Shaggy dog story Piccolo Junior Saga Salad Fingers Police dog Time Out of Mind The Fairly OddParents Vulcan (Star Trek) Dog Billboard Hot 100 Social rule The Price Is Right Extreme Programming Si